videos.headline: Sanders runs 14 yards for 1st Penn State TD
videos.description: Miles Sanders powers his way up the middle for a 14-yard touchdown.

videos.headline: Corbin runs up the middle for 2-yard Illini TD
videos.description: Reggie Corbin goes in untouched for a 2-yard touchdown to tie Illinois with Penn State 7-7.

videos.headline: Sanders runs in for his 2nd TD
videos.description: Miles Sanders goes up the middle for a 2-yard touchdown.

videos.headline: McSorley connects with Freiermuth for TD
videos.description: Trace McSorley fakes the handoff and throws to Pat Freiermuth for a 5-yard touchdown.

videos.headline: Smalling hauls in 6-yard Illini TD
videos.description: M.J. Rivers II connects with Ricky Smalling in the endzone to cut into Penn State's lead.

videos.headline: Illinois takes lead on trick play
videos.description: Wide receiver Trenard Davis takes the reverse and connects with Ricky Smalling for a 17-yard touchdown.

videos.headline: Sanders breaks tackle, takes off for 48-yard TD
videos.description: Miles Sanders scores his third touchdown of the game as he breaks off a 48-yard run.

videos.headline: McSorley delivers 16-yard TD
videos.description: Trace McSorley steps up in the pocket and throws a strike to Juwan Johnson to extend Penn State's lead.

videos.headline: McSorley throws 3rd TD of game
videos.description: Trace McSorley throws a back-shoulder pass to KJ Hamler for a 21-yard touchdown.

videos.headline: Slade breaks off 61-yard TD run
videos.description: Ricky Slade burns the Illini defense up the middle for a 61-yard touchdown.

videos.headline: Penn State takes off in 2nd half to avoid a stumble
videos.description: The Nittany Lions score 42 points in the second half and crush Illinois 63-24. Miles Sanders runs for three touchdowns and 200 yards in the win.
